text:
Share Anthony Mudine v Danny Green: Quade Cooper boxing opponent Jack McInnes - Yahoo7 Wallabies star Quade Cooper returns to the boxing ring on the undercard of Anthony Mundine's rematch with Danny Green on Friday night. Close Green knocks Tony Mundine's hat off UP NEXT VIDEO Green knocks Tony Mundine's hat off. Source: The Advertiser/Facebook Green knocks Tony Mundine's hat off 
It'll be Cooper's third professional boxing bout when he takes on Jack McInnes at Adelaide Oval. 
Cooper and McInnes weighed-in for their fight on Thursday and there was a stark difference in the physiques of both men. Cooper and McInnes. Image: Twitter 
While the professional rugby star is in great shape, his opponent really isn't. 
A 22-year-old fighter from Queensland, McInnes has 55 professional fights in Muay Thai kickboxing and cage boxing, and two losses as a pro boxer. 
THE TIME HAS COME: Green ready for Mundine revenge 
When pictures emerged from Thursday's weigh-in, fans took to social media with some pretty harsh criticism for both men. Anyone know why Quade Cooper is fighting the fat kid from Hey Dad? #MundineGreen2 pic.twitter.com/632oBFDmhu
